8:T41f7,<p>You’ll treat any site like a <strong>controlled experiment</strong>: assign roles, map hazards and noise, and document baseline conditions before you start. Use <strong>calibrated EMF meters</strong>, high‑quality WAV audio, and thermal/IR cameras, logging settings, timestamps, and chain of custody for every file. Attempt to recreate anomalies, rule out mundane causes, and demand <strong>independent corroboration</strong>. Preserve original data and metadata, keep methods repeatable, and remain skeptical — follow this approach and you’ll learn how to gather <strong>verifiable, testable evidence</strong>.</p>
<h2 id="key-takeaways">Key Takeaways</h2>
<ul>
